==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cadger
<hw>Cadg"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Cadge</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos>, cf. <er>Codger</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A packman or itinerant huckster.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who gets his living by trickery or
begging.</def> <mark>[Prov. or Slang]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧The gentleman
<xex>cadger</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dickens.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cadger</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Cadger
<hw>Cadg"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>cagier</ets> one who
catches hawks. Cf. <er>Cage</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Hawking)</fld> <def>One
who carries hawks on a cadge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cadgy</ent>⟦br⟧
